            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "Whole-Home Standby Generator Option: Advantages of whole-home generators: Automatic operation (starts within 10-20 seconds of power loss—whether you're home or away), permanent fuel source (natural gas or propane—no refueling needed during outages), whole-home or selected circuits backup (powers everything or prioritized circuits), automatic transfer switch (safe, UL-listed switching between grid and generator power), weather-protected (purpose-built outdoor enclosures), quieter operation (60-68 decibels—similar to normal conversation), professional installation with permits and inspections, long runtime (can run days or weeks during extended outages), increased home value (appraisals reflect $10,000-20,000 value increase), and insurance discounts (many carriers offer 5-15% premium reductions). Disadvantages: Higher upfront cost ($11,500-14,500 installed for typical Corona de Tucson homes), annual maintenance required ($200-350/year to maintain warranty), installation complexity (permits, gas lines, concrete pad, transfer switch), and fixed location (can't take portable). Whole-home generators are ideal for: Well-dependent properties (no power = no water), equestrian properties (horse health requires continuous water access), medical equipment needs, home office with income-dependent uptime, frequent travelers (generator works whether you're home or not), families with young children or elderly members, properties storing valuable perishables or medications, and anyone valuing convenience and peace of mind over upfront cost."
